addChildToFamily

void addChildToFamily(TAuthToken token,
                      long adminId,
                      TChild child)
                      throws AuthorizationException.InvalidToken,
                             AuthorizationException.NotPermitted,
                             OperationException.ChildAlreadyExists,
                             OperationException.NotFound,
                             OperationException.DuplicateName,
                             GatewayException,
                             PersistException,
                             ServiceException
Add a child to the specified account

Parameters:
token - current admintool auth token
adminId - id of the account to which the child should be added.
child - details of the child to add
Throws:
AuthorizationException.InvalidToken - if the admintool login token is not valid or has expired
AuthorizationException.NotPermitted - if the current admintool user is not allowed to make that request.
OperationException.ChildAlreadyExists - if the mdn specified has already been added to this account.
OperationException.NotFound - if account information for the specified mdn could not be found.
OperationException.DuplicateName - if the child's name is a duplicate of another child's.
GatewayException - if we cannot communicate with an external service, probably the carrier's account system
PersistException - if there is a database issue
ServiceException - in the case of any other error
